<br>
Personally I think your best choice is between these 4:<br>
<br>
Double Riposte: (3 skill levels) - This ability gives the Warrior a chance for a double riposte any time he successfully ripostes. The first skill level gives the Warrior a 15% chance for a Double Riposte, the second skill level raises that chance to 30% and the third skill level makes the chance 50%.<br>
<br>
Flurry: (3 skill levels - - Prerequisite: 3 skill levels of the Melee Archetype ability Combat Fury) - This ability gives the Warrior a chance of taking two extra attacks with his primary hand whenever he successfully hits an opponent.<br>
<br>
Ambidexterity: (1 skill level - cost 9 skill points) - This ability makes the Warrior more skilled with the use of two weapons by increasing his chance to successfully dual wield.<br>
<br>
Warcry: (3 skill levels - Prerequisite: 3 skill levels of the Melee Archetype ability Fear Resistance) - This ability allows the Warrior to make everyone in his group immune to fear for a limited time. Each skill level with this ability increases the duration of the immunity. The Refresh Timer for this ability is 72 minutes (one day of game time).<br>
<br>
Warcry would be awesome on dragon raids but that really depends on how long the skill lasts, if it only has a limited range and lasts as long as the fearless disc then I'd say it sucks.<br>
<br>
Just my 2 cents I'd suggest seeing if you can find it on a message board, I'm still unsure of which I should do for my cleric. <p><center><a href="http://www.silentsentinels.com"><img src="http://www.vanitey.com/sigs/sig2.jpg" border=0 align=bottom></a></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#F5F5DC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uvisteme.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Visteme</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://wwp.icq.com/scripts/online.dll?icq=116960908&img=5" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Desert Madman</span><br>  Posts: 55<br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/17/01 11:35:26 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Has anyone seen info on adavance skill points?</span><hr size=1> yah, warcry and flurry are pretty nice, but both of those require 12 points in a specific arch, and well i didn't put my 12 points into the prerequesites for those, think i may go ambidexterity, then work on those arch abilities.. <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=7617>Visteme</a>
